Crossposted-To: comp.windows.x.i386unix
From: jon@robots.ox.ac.uk (Jon Tombs)
Subject: Re: 2MB vs 1MB on 801 S3 ?
Date: Fri, 5 Nov 1993 10:41:00 GMT

In article <1993Nov4.132035.12676@news.uit.no> chris@stud.cs.uit.no writes:
>I am currenty running Xfree 2.0 S3-server, on a Actix GraphicsENGINE 32 plus
>with 1 MB dram (801 at-bus card). 
>I was just wondering if anyone has a clue to how much performanse gain
>it will be to updrade to 2 MB...?

All off screen memory will be used as cache, it would mean you cache pixmaps
of upto 256x256, and several hundred more fonts than you would ever want.
If you spen a lot of time moving big pixmaps around then this might be
important to you. But the caching of the xfree86-2.0 servers is still far to
primative to make much advantage of the extra ram (should improve with time
though).

>Ofcause the resolution is importante; I'm running 1024x768x256 in about
>80Hz NI mode. I plan to keen this resolution even if I upgrade.


You can of course keep this resolution, but use a 1280x1024 virtual screen,
helps xfig fit :-)


>My card is good for 57000 Xstones on my 486-33DX, 16MB.
>( This test was done on the X386 1.2 S3-server ).

If you have 60ns dram then you should be able to get a little more with
xfree86-2.0, I would expect a 45ns dram card to get >80k xstones.


Jon.



