From: jon@robots.ox.ac.uk (Jon Tombs)
Subject: Re: XFree86 2.0 Locks up computer
Date: Fri, 5 Nov 1993 10:49:03 GMT

In article <1993Nov2.213658.27289@hellgate.utah.edu> tevans%sunset.cs.utah.edu@cs.utah.edu (Terry Evans) writes:
>  I just installed XFree86 2.0 and pl13o of the kernel.
>I am currently using the most recent version of tvtwm and everything
>works just fine until I try to access the pull down menus by using the
>mouse on the root display.  Once I try, the entire computer locks up!
>I can't do anything at that point except reboot.

From the assounding lack of information you have guiven, I would guess you
have a VLB machine with a S3/805 fitted. The problem sounds like a waitstate
mismatch of other VLB related problem.

add :
Option "nomemaccess" 
to your Xconfig and the server will only use IO access.

>  I didn't have these problems with XS3.

XS3 was especially broken when it came to localbus, it didn't even try to 
do didrect memory access, and programs the S3 wrongly anyway...

>  Does anybody have any ideas?

Add more detail and post to comp.windows.x.i386unix if this doesn't fix
the problem.

Jon.

